!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

hike /haɪk/

(hiking,hiked,hikes) 

1. N-COUNT A hike is a long walk in the country, especially one that you go on for pleasure. 远足 

例： The site is reached by a 30-minute hike through dense forest. 要花30分钟徒步穿过密林才能到达那个地方。 

2. V-I If you hike , you go for a long walk in the country. 远足 

例： You could hike through the Fish River Canyon – it's entirely up to you. 你可以远足穿越菲什干河大峡谷–这全由你自己决定。 

3. hiking N-UNCOUNT 远足 

例： ...some harder, more strenuous hiking on cliff pathways. …在悬崖峭壁的小路上进行的更艰难、更费力的长途行走。 

4. N-COUNT A hike is a sudden or large increase in prices, rates, taxes, or quantities. 突然上涨 [非正式] 

例： ...a sudden 1.75 percent hike in interest rates. …利率突涨1.75%。 

5. V-T To hike prices, rates, taxes, or quantities means to increase them suddenly or by a large amount. 使大幅上升 [非正式] 

例： It has now been forced to hike its rates by 5.25 percent. 它现在被迫将其税率提高5.25%。 

6. PHRASAL VERB Hike up means the same as . 使大幅上升 

例： The insurers have started hiking up premiums by huge amounts. 保险公司已经开始大幅度地提高保险费。

</div>

